William L. Flagg, Respondent, v. Henry Prouse Cooper, Appellant. Decided May 2, 1887. Appeal by defendant from an order denying a motion to set aside a sale, made under execution in this action. . George H. Foster, for appellant. William L. Flagg, for respondent.-

-Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., and O’Gorman, J.

Opinion Per Curiam.

Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements to be taxed.
